:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"http://wpstorecart.com/?p=723\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:448:\"wpStoreCart has seen nothing but constant, full time development since March of 2010. 14 months, and over 35 releases later, we&#8217;re still working long nights to try and bring you the very best WordPress ecommerce plugin possible. To that end, I wanted to share with you what the next two big releases will be. Next&#8230; <a class=\"continue_reading\" href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/announcing-wpstorecart-2-3-and-3-0/\">Continue reading &#187;</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2487:\"<p>wpStoreCart has seen nothing but constant, full time development since March of 2010.  14 months, and over 35 releases later, we&#8217;re still working long nights to try and bring you the very best WordPress ecommerce plugin possible.  To that end, I wanted to share with you what the next two big releases will be.  Next week, we&#8217;re hoping to finish wpStoreCart 2.3, which adds social media sharing, image galleries, and light boxes.  We will continue to release additional 2.3.x versions throughout May and June, all leading up to the big release of wpStoreCart 3 in late June (possibly July if there are delays.)  Full details are below:</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-723\"></span><br />\nWhat&#8217;s new in the upcoming wpStoreCart 2.3.x branch later this May:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Social media sharing of products (2.3.0)</li>\n<li>Optional lightbox for viewing product images (2.3.0)</li>\n<li>Image galleries with unlimited number of images per product (2.3.0)</li>\n<li>Customers will have the ability to sort products by Low Price, High Price, Newest, and Oldest (2.3.x)</li>\n<li>Tax options will be exposed (2.3.x)</li>\n<li>New Payment Failed page (2.3.x)</li>\n<li>Ability to delete and rename product uploads from the Download tab when editing a product (2.3.x)</li>\n</ul>\n<p />\n<br />\nWhat&#8217;s upcoming in wpStoreCart 3, coming June:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Customers can use filters to see products only from specific manufacturers </li>\n<li>New widgets added: manufacturers, payments accepted, fancy newest products, and fancy most popular </li>\n<li>Two new WordPress user roles: Customer and Merchant</li>\n<li>Product groups and multi-item packages.  Sell groups of your products together as a single product</li>\n<li>3 different cart styles, and multiple checkout styles configurable </li>\n<li>Video and audio players for mp3, flv, and more</li>\n<li>Optionally, user must accept a license agreement, terms of service, privacy policy, and other legal issues</li>\n<li>Bulk, multi-item discounts</li>\n<li>Payment Gateway API to create your own custom payment gateways</li>\n<li>Shipping Gateway API to create your own shipping service integration</li>\n<li>Temporary sale prices per product</li>\n<li>Percentage off sales for the entire store, specific categories, and/or individual products</li>\n<li>Redesigned admin panel, with more inline Ajax editing through out</li>\n<li>Coupons can now be limited to 1 or more uses only before they expire</li>\n<li>WPMU and BuddyPress support!</li>\n</ul>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s: