ction-wp_get_current_user_wordpress_3/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:103:\"http://wpstorecart.com/fatal-error-call-to-undefined-function-wp_get_current_user_wordpress_3/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 17 Mar 2011 20:45:39 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Troubleshooting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"http://wpstorecart.com/?p=504\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:550:\"UPDATE: No one should get this error. It was present in pre-release versions of 2.1.9, and has been patched in the final version of 2.1.9. I added the following code to wpstorecart.php on line 49: if (file_exists(ABSPATH . \'wp-includes/pluggable.php\')) { require_once(ABSPATH . \'wp-includes/pluggable.php\'); } If you&#8217;re running wpStoreCart (or any other WordPress plugin for that&#8230; <a class=\"continue_reading\" href=\"http://wpstorecart.com/fatal-error-call-to-undefined-function-wp_get_current_user_wordpress_3/\">Continue reading &#187;</a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2485:\"<p><strong>UPDATE:</strong> No one should get this error.  It was present in pre-release versions of 2.1.9, and has been patched in the final version of 2.1.9.  I added the following code to wpstorecart.php on line 49:<br />\n<code>if (file_exists(ABSPATH . \'wp-includes/pluggable.php\')) {<br />\n    require_once(ABSPATH . \'wp-includes/pluggable.php\');<br />\n}</code></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re running wpStoreCart (or any other WordPress plugin for that matter) and come across this error:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Fatal error: Call to undefined function wp_get_current_user() in C:PORTABLESEasyPHP-5.3.3wwwwordpresswp-includescapabilities.php on line 1028</p></blockquote>\n<p><span id=\"more-504\"></span><br />\nthen the only solution I was able to find was to edit /wp-includes/capabilities.php and replace this code, on line 1:<br />\n<code>&lt;?PHP</code></p>\n<p>with this code:<br />\n<code>&lt;?PHP<br />\nrequire_once(\'pluggable.php\');<br />\n</code></p>\n<p>Note that anytime you update WordPress you will have to recreate this edit.</p>\n<p>Now you may be thinking to yourself, why should I edit a core WordPress file just to run wpStoreCart?  Well, the issue goes much deeper than that, and in my opinion appears to be a bug with WordPress itself.  This bug has plagued <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://buddypress.org/forums/topic/fatal-error-call-to-undefined-function-wp_get_current_user\">BuddyPress</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/support/topic/fatal-error-call-to-undefined-function-wp_get_current_user-5\">WPMU</a>,  and <a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.google.com/search?sourceid=chrome&#038;ie=UTF-8&#038;q=Fatal+error:+Call+to+undefined+function+wp_get_current_user()+i#sclient=psy&#038;hl=en&#038;safe=off&#038;source=hp&#038;q=Fatal+error%3A+Call+to+undefined+function+wp_get_current_user()+&#038;aq=f&#038;aqi=g1&#038;aql=&#038;oq=&#038;pbx=1&#038;bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.&#038;fp=87b61fcb467d957c\">scores of other plugins</a>.</p>\n<p>Anyway, essentially the problem is that WordPress isn&#8217;t ready for user authentication early enough in the file chain, resulting in this error.  It was sporadic when it happened to me, I hadn&#8217;t changed anything.  I&#8217;m trying to find what triggered the issue for me (it may not have even been wpStoreCart that caused the issue) and see if there isn&#8217;t a better way besides editing a core WordPress file.  Just thought I&#8217;d post this as a heads up though.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"http://wpstorecart.com/fatal-error-call-to-undefined-function-wp_get_current_user_wordpress_3/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n	\n		\n		\n		\n	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"A New, Free Premium Ecommerce WordPress Template: wpStoreCartTheme\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"http://wpstorecart.com/a-new-free-premium-ecommerce-wordpress-template-wpstorecarttheme/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"x