ced in beta 1, as well as additional bugs that we think are affecting a large number of users out there. Today we&#8217;re happy to announce the second round of beta (and hopefully the last).</p>\n<p>For a full list of features in this new version check out the <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-plugin-3-8-8-beta-ready-for-consumption/\">3.8.8-beta 1</a>  blog post!</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-241003\" title=\"Revamped sales log\" src=\"http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/saleslog2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"331\" /></p>\n<p>Issues introduced in 3.8.8-beta 1 that are fixed in beta 2:</p>\n<pre>* Fixed: Wrong position of new field row if the previous field has\n  option panel opened (Settings-&gt;Checkout). Also fixed several jslint\n  issues.\n* Fixed: When stock is limited, rather than hiding stock column of\n  variations in product edit page, disable the input field instead.\n* Fixed: Pressing \"Save\" for inline variation editing kills variation\n  title.\n* Fixed: CSS position for Add Tracking ID label is incorrect.\n* Fixed: In Sales Log page, summary line does not get updated when\n  sales log status is changed.</pre>\n<p>Additional issues that we fixed:</p>\n<pre>* All issues which have been fixed in 3.8.7.6 but not in 3.8.8-beta1\n* New: Improved Digital Download Product UI\n* Change: PayPal Standard settings now just offer dropdown of\n  \"live\" / \"sandbox\" rather than URL entry.\n* Fix: %-based shipping cost is not working internationally.\n* Fix: 3.7 -&gt; 3.8 Database Upgrade Routine causes some products with\n  variations to display a $0.00 price.\n* Fix: Incompatibility with Genesis framework in Product Edit page.\n* Fix: Mandatory fields in user_log_functions.php are not properly\n  validated.\n* Fix: Memory improvement for productfeed.\n* Fix: Purchase logs have incorrect time if a timezone is specified\n  in Settings-&gt;General.\n* Fix: Summary line does not get updated when sales log status is changed.</pre>\n<p>At this stage, we can say that the release is relatively stable. Feel free to play with it or develop new projects on it. However, do not use this on a production site unless you know what you&#8217;re doing and of course, ALWAYS back up your site.  (We know people say this often without giving advice on HOW to do so, but we like <a title=\"Backup Buddy\" href=\"http://pluginbuddy.com/purchase/backupbuddy/\">Backup Buddy</a>).</p>\n<p>Please let us know if you run into any issues with this beta release. You can either post your issues directly in the comment section below,or  on <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/forums/forum/alpha-beta-release-candidates/3-8-8-beta/\">our support forum</a>. Of course, we always welcome the community to participate in contributing to the WP e-Commerce plugin, if you&#8217;re interested, sign up for our <a title=\"WordPress e-Commerce developers\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/wordpress-e-commerce-plugin\">developers newsletter</a>.</p>\n<p>We look forward to pushing out a first release candidate next week.</p>\n<p><strong>&gt;&gt; <a href=\"http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.8-beta2.zip\">Click here to download 3.8.8-beta2</a></strong></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-8-beta2/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"15\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base