 fix, 3.8.7.6 also includes bug fixes for several [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Gary Cao\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1448:\"<p>Hi everyone!</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re happy to release WP e-Commerce 3.8.7.6.</p>\n<p>This is a <strong>mandatory</strong> security and bug fix release. Alan Schneider helped us fix a <strong>critical</strong> security vulnerability that affects all sites running WPEC 3.8.x. Please upgrade your 3.8.x sites to 3.8.7.6 as soon as possible.</p>\n<p>Besides the security fix, 3.8.7.6 also includes bug fixes for several issues, most notably compatibility issues with WordPress 3.3. Please <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/changelog/\">refer to our changelog</a> for the list of issues addressed in this release.</p>\n<p>We would like to thank <a href=\"http://www.ozwald.fr/\">Alan Schneider</a>, <a href=\"http://www.leewillis.co.uk/\">Lee Willis</a>, <a href=\"http://om4.com.au/\">James Collins</a> and <a href=\"http://www.benhuson.co.uk/\">Ben Huson</a> for contributing to this release.</p>\n<p><strong>How to upgrade</strong></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re running 3.8.x, simply use WordPress automatic upgrade. If that doesn&#8217;t work for you, <a href=\"http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.7.6.zip\">download the package manually</a>, extract it and upload to <code>wp-content/plugins</code>.</p>\n<p>As usual, <strong>please back up your database and files before attempting the upgrade</strong>. That&#8217;s something any responsible administrators do before upgrading any plugins or even WordPress core itself.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0