, we know we can’t please everyone but we’re making 2012 “The Year of the User”. To start, we really want to know how you feel about us, about the experience of using WPEC, about the problems you might have had, the successes, how you feel about pricing, support, features, the roadmap and where WPEC is heading. Infact, we want to hear from you whether you’re a user, developer or someone who doesn’t even use WPEC anymore. If you’ve got a complaint, now’s the time to air it. Sure, we want to hear the good stuff, but those items don’t need fixing.</p>\n<p>We’re going to take this <a href=\"http://650844.polldaddy.com/s/2011wpecsurvey\">survey</a> really seriously and use it to help determine where WPEC is headed. You may feel your vote isn’t weighty when it comes to elections, the economic outlook or which came first, the chicken or the egg&#8230; but we promise it will be heard here.</p>\n<p>As a thank you for filling out the three minute survey, we’re going to throw a few iPods into the pool and send them to three random respondees.</p>\n<p>» <a href=\"http://650844.polldaddy.com/s/2011wpecsurvey\">Take the survey</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/occupywpec-tell-us-what-you-really-think/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"WP e-Commerce 3.8.7.5 security release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-5-security-release/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-5-security-release/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 06 Jan 2012 08:43:26 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"GetShopped News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Security\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WP e-Commerce Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://getshopped.org/?p=245029\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:321:\"Hi everyone! First of all, happy new year! 2012 will be a very exciting year for WPEC users. Some big stuff is coming up for this year, but that&#8217;s for another post (we prefer to show you rather than to tell you It&#8217;s going to be a pleasant surprise for sure). Anyways, our friend Alain Schneider helped [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Gary Cao\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2577:\"<p>Hi everyone!</p>\n<p>First of all, happy new year! 2012 will be a very exciting year for WPEC users. Some big stuff is coming up for this year, but that&#8217;s for another post (we prefer to show you rather than to tell you <img src=\'http://getshopped.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\' alt=\';)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' />  It&#8217;s going to be a pleasant surprise for sure).</p>\n<p>Anyways, our friend <a href=\"http://www.ozwald.fr/\">Alain Schneider</a> helped us plug a Cross Site Scripting (XSS) security hole that&#8217;s affecting all 3.8.x and 3.7.8.x installations. The severity of this issue is moderate, so we highly recommend that you upgrade to 3.8.7.5 and 3.7.8.3 respectively (by &#8220;highly recommend&#8221;, we really mean we&#8217;re begging you to upgrade; security issues are no trivial stuff!).</p>\n<p>We would also like to thank <a href=\"http://www.whitefirdesign.com/\">White Fir Design</a> for organizing the <a href=\"http://www.whitefirdesign.com/about/wordpress-security-bug-bounty-program.html\">WordPress Security Bug Bounty Program</a>. Most of our recent security fixes came out of that program, and we can&#8217;t say enough how grateful we are! It&#8217;s impressive that a company is willing to go that far to improve the quality of WordPress open source plugins. But it&#8217;s also shocking that such a program is not heavily promoted and talked about by WordPress community. If you&#8217;re interested, <a href=\"http://www.whitefirdesign.com/about/wordpress-security-bug-bounty-program.html\">head over there and participate</a>!</p>\n<p><strong>How to upgrade</strong></p>\n<p>For 3.8.x users, you can use WordPress&#8217; automatic upgrade feature. Or you can <a href=\"http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.7.5.zip\">download the package manually</a>, extract it and upload to <code>wp-content/plugins</code>.</p>\n<p>For 3.7.8.x users, <strong>do not use automatic upgrade</strong>. Instead, <a href=\"http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.7.8.3.zip\">download the 3.7.8.3 package here</a>, extract it and upload to <code>wp-content/plugins</code>. It&#8217;s important to note that we no longer officially support 3.7.8. We recommend that you upgrade to the latest 3.8.x to enjoy all the new features and bug fixes.</p>\n<p>We don&#8217;t want to sound like a broken record, but <strong>please backup your database and files before upgrading, just in case</strong>. In fact, you should not only do this with WP e-Commerce updates, but also with WordPress core or any other plugins&#8217; updates.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-7-5-security-release/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"8\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"New docs.getshopped.org are up and running – helped made possible by LightSpeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a: