y talked about but poorly understood. It only takes seconds for one of these diseases to claim its victim. Our instructor, Donn Kropp, RN, BSN, uncovers the mysteries surrounding these ailments. Do you have the knowledge to help those who suffer from asthma, pneumonia and COPD?','Respiratory System Part 2: Asthma, Pneumonia, COPD','Millions of Americans suffer from asthma, pneumonia and COPD. These common respiratory diseases are frequently talked about but poorly understood. It only takes seconds for one of these diseases to claim its victim. Our instructor, Donn Kropp, RN, BSN, uncovers the mysteries surrounding these ailments. Do you have the knowledge to help those who suffer from asthma, pneumonia and COPD?  ','inherit','closed','closed','','176-revision-6','','','2011-11-28 10:13:47','2011-11-28 18:13:47','',176,'http://clickplayceu.com/2011/11/176-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(220,1,'2011-08-24 05:55:21','2011-08-24 05:55:21','','Respiratory Part 2','','inherit','closed','closed','','respiratory2','','','2011-08-24 05:55:21','2011-08-24 05:55:21','',176,'http://clickplayceu.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Respiratory2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(180,1,'2011-08-23 04:45:29','2011-08-23 04:45:29','It only takes seconds for a respiratory emergency to claim its victim. Do you have a foundational understanding of the respiratory system to be able to prevent and manage respiratory related problems? Take an exciting journey through the respiratory system. This course sets the ground work for you to understand various respiratory diseases and conditions.\r\n\r\nTo breathe is to live. The Greek word for breath is pneuma and can be translated as spirit, soul or life. Breathing is an activity that we perform seventeen to twenty thousand times a day. The most important function of breathing is to provide gas exchange. This means oxygen goes into our bodies and carbon dioxide comes out. Our bodies have the amazing ability to control and regulate our breathing patterns based on our needs. Breath is life. Without the activity of inspiration (breathing in) and expiration (breathing out) life ceases to occur. We need oxygen to live, in fact, our bodies only last a few minutes without it.\r\n\r\nWhen you breathe in air its journey starts at the nostrils. Once air passes through the nasal cavity its next destination is the pharynx. Learn more about the exciting tale of the oxygen molecule and the respiratory system by taking this course. Donn Kropp, our expert registered nurse, will be sure to entertain and teach you the importance of having a comprehensive understanding of the respiratory system.\r\n\r\n<strong>Course Objectives</strong>\r\nUpon completion of this course you will be able to:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Describe oxygen and carbon dioxide and their roles</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the Anatomy and Physiology of the Respiratory System</li>\r\n	<li>Describe the mechanism and function of breathing</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Chapter Content</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Introduction</li>\r\n	<li>Objectives</li>\r\n	<li>O2 and CO2</li>\r\n	<li>Anatomy and Physiology</li>\r\n	<li>Mechanism and Function</li>\r\n	<li>Conclusion</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Course Approvals</strong>: This course is pending approval by the following boards\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>NAB: This educational offering has been reviewed by the National Continuing Education Review Service (NCERS) of the National Association of Boards of Examiners of Long Term Care Administrators (NAB).</li>\r\n	<li>California Adult Residential Facility (ARF) Vendor No. 2000149-735-2 Course Approval No. ____________</li>\r\n	<li>Residential Care Facility for the Elderly (RCFE) Vendor No. 2000149-740-2 Course Approval No._________</li>\r\n	<li>Group Home (GH) Vendor No. 2000149-730-2Â  Course Approval No. __________</li>\r\n	<li>CA &amp; FL Board of Registered Nursing: CA Provider No.__________Â  FL Provider No.________</li>\r\n	<li>California Board of Vocational Nursing Provider No.___________</li>\r\